               (95\% CI 0.865-1.204), P = 0.811) or mortality within 24 h (OR
               1.049 (95\% CI 0.829-1.327), P = 0.693). However, male gender
               was associated with an increased likelihood for ICU admission in
               the overall group (OR 1.205 (95\% CI 1.046-1.388), P = 0.010).
               CONCLUSION: The current study shows that in this population of
               severely injured patients, female sex is associated with a lower
               in-hospital mortality rate among those aged 16- to 44-years.
               Furthermore, female sex is independently associated with an
               overall decreased likelihood for ICU admission. More research is
               needed to examine the physiologic background of this protective
               effect of female sex in severe trauma.",
