               American College of Surgeons NSQIP database from 2005 to 2011. A
               total of 8761 patients representing 91 orthopaedic trauma
               procedures were identified and included in analysis after
               selection. Logistic regressions were conducted to identify the
               predictive ability of ASA on the likelihood of readmission for
               patients in each anatomic category (upper extremity,
               pelvis/acetabulum, lower extremity) and the combined study
               population. RESULTS: The ASA physical status proved the
               strongest predictor of 30-day readmission for the selected
               orthopaedic trauma procedures. After controlling for age,
               gender, race, and medical comorbidities that were shown to be
               significant independent risk factors for readmission, ASA score
